Conflicts: syslinux-common (>= 3:6.00)
Enhances: extlinux
Description: minimal theme of boot loaders
 SYSLINUX is a collection of boot loaders which operates off Linux ext2/3/4 or
 btrfs filesystems, MS-DOS FAT filesystems, network servers using PXE firmware,
 or from CD-ROMs.
 .
 This package contains the minimal graphical bootloader theme.
